   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON FIVE THE REAL SIGNIFICANCE OF MAN'S FALL Scripture Reading: Gen 3:1-8; Rom 5:12, 14-16; 7:14b, 17-18, 20-21; Eph 2:1, 5a; 4:18; 1 Cor 15:22a OUTLINE Not only: Transgressing against God's commandment Rom 5:14b.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Falling under God's condemnation Rom 5:16b.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Estranging man from God Gen 3:8; Eph 4:18.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Spoiling man from fulfilling God's purpose: Expressing God in His image.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Representing God with His dominion.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>But also: Receiving Satan's evil thought, feeling, and will into the inward parts of man's soul Gen 3:1, 4-5.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Taking the tree of knowledge into the members of man's body Gen 3:6: Man's body being transmuted into flesh Rom 7:18a.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Satan becoming sin within man Rom 7:14b, 17, 20.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Sin acting as evil in man Rom 7:21.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Deadening man's spirit Eph 2:1, 5a.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Letting sin enter into man Rom 5:12a.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Making man the victim of death Rom 5:12b, 14a; 1 Cor 15:22a.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Focus:Through man's fall Satan's personality became one with man's soul, and he was taken into man's body to be sin working as evil in man's fleshly members.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>In the previous lesson we saw Satan's plot to spoil man.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>In this lesson we want to see the real significance of man's fall.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Among most Christians the understanding of man's fall is altogether inadequate.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>For this lesson we need to read the verses in the scripture reading attentively, slowly, and carefully so that we can be impressed with these portions of the Word.</S>
   </TEXT>
